# Tech stack

- SvelteKit + TypeScript (Svelte 5 with runes: $state, $derived, $effect, $props)
- No CSS framework - hand-written CSS with CSS variables (see src/app.css)
- No external UI component library
- Assets in `static/`:
  - `quappe.png` / `favicon.png`: logo + browser tab icon
  - `dialog_network.png`: About-page visual


# Layout (desktop)

Three-column shell:

```
┌────────────┬──────────────────────┬───────────────┐
│ Sidebar-L  │   Main content       │  Sidebar-R    │
│            │                      │               │
│ Brand      │                      │ (top spacer)  │
│ Logo+Title │                      │               │
│ ────────── │                      │ Budget panel  │
│ Trending   │                      │ Activity      │
│ Top        │                      │  streamgraph  │
│ My Theses  │                      │ Complexity    │
│ [+ New]    │                      │  slider       │
│ ────────── │                      │ Settings link │
│ About      │                      │               │
└────────────┴──────────────────────┴───────────────┘
```

- Left sidebar (220px): Brand + primary nav (Trending / Top / My Theses / New Thesis button). Separator. Secondary nav (About).
- Right sidebar (280px): Budget (3-bucket progress bars), compact Activity streamgraph, Complexity slider, Settings link. Top spacer mirrors brand height for visual balance.
- Both sidebars are sticky.

## Responsive
- <= 1024px: right sidebar hides (budget still visible via other means later).
- <= 768px: left sidebar becomes a hamburger drawer, topbar with brand+menu appears.


# Views

## Landing (/) - "Trending"
- Page head: title + subtitle.
- Category tiles (drill-down): size scales by count. Click filters. "Clear filter" button when active.
- Grid of ThesisCards (2 columns on desktop).
- Complexity slider limits how many are shown.

## Top (/top)
- Same layout as landing.
- Ordered by all-time support count.
- Each card has a rank badge (#1, #2, ...).
- Category selector also available (drill-down).

## My Theses (/my)
- Theses the current anonymous user created or voted on.

## Thesis detail (/thesis/[id])
- Title, description, categories.
- Vote row for the thesis itself.
- Author-only Edit button. Anyone with admin rights can Archive.
- Two columns: **Supporting** (green) | **Rejecting** (red).
  - Each has an "+ Add" button (uses respective budget bucket).
  - Arguments show fork icon (create fork) and, if author, edit icon.
  - Forks display "based on: ..." note and are connected by red dashed thread to parent.

## About (/about)
- Left (220px, small): dialog_network.png in card frame.
- Right: Purpose, How it works, Rules (highlighted yellow cards), What this is not, CTA.

## Settings (/settings)
- Anonymous ID display.
- Role badge (MVP: everyone is admin).
- Categories management (add/remove/reset).
- About section.


# Components

- `Logo.svelte`: renders `/quappe.png`, configurable size.
- `ThesisCard.svelte`: card with title, description, categories, badges (argument count + lifecycle), heat-colored left border, vote row.
- `ArgumentCard.svelte`: card with fork-note (if applicable), content, primary evidence badge + source-list (chips linking to detected URLs), vote row + fork/edit icons. **Users do NOT pick evidence type** — it is derived server-side.
- `VoteRow.svelte`: shared voting UI. Shows abbreviated counts (K/M/B) and support/reject/neutral buttons. Clicking a button once = weight 1. Clicking again on the same type increments weight up to 3 (each extra weight costs 1 budget). Clicking the same type at max weight retracts the vote.
- `ForkLines.svelte`: SVG overlay drawing red dashed bezier curves between forked arguments in a column.
- `ActivityGraph.svelte`: streamgraph (pastel green/purple/gray/red), symmetric around centerline, 5-day rolling average.
- `ComplexitySlider.svelte`: single slider bound to `complexityBoundsStore.min`..`max` (configurable in Settings).


# UI Basic Requirements

- Lightweight
- State of the art 2026
- Focus on snappiness
- Focus on readability
- Fully anonymous (no usernames visible)


# Design tokens (CSS variables in src/app.css)

- Neutral background (#fafafa), white surface, subtle borders.
- Accent: primary indigo (#4f46e5).
- Vote colors: support green (#16a34a), reject red (#dc2626), neutral gray.
- Pastel palette for activity streamgraph.
- Monospaced font for numbers/IDs.


# Complexity slider

- Present in right sidebar on all views (except settings).
- Affects both list view AND graph view.
- Bounds are configurable in Settings (`complexityBoundsStore`), persisted in localStorage.
- **Default bounds**:
  - Theses: min 3, max 62 (golden ratio ~61.8).
  - Arguments per stance per Thesis: min 3, max 7.
- **Hard limits** (safety cap admins can't exceed):
  - Theses: 3 to 200.
  - Arguments: 3 to 20.
- Simplified language mode at low complexity (later).
- TL;DR summaries generated at low complexity (later).


# Fork visualization

- Fork icon on ArgumentCard opens the argument form pre-filled with the source content.
- On submit: new argument gets `forked_from_id` pointing to the source.
- In the argument column, a **red dashed bezier curve** is drawn from the parent's bottom-left to the fork's top-left (via `ForkLines.svelte`).
- The forked card also shows a small "based on: ..." note in red at the top.


# Interaction patterns

- Voting toggles: same type+weight twice = retract.
- Weighted voting: click a vote button again to raise weight (up to ×3). Each extra weight costs 1 budget point.
- Large vote counts are abbreviated: values ≥ 10 000 shown as `12k`, `1.5M`, `3.2B`.
- ThesisCard: entire card is a link to the detail page; vote buttons stop propagation.
- Fork keeps the same stance as the source (support stays support, reject stays reject).
- Editing does not cost budget. Creating and forking do. Weight votes cost from the matching stance bucket.
- Anonymous UUID is stored in localStorage. Same browser = same identity.
- Categories are shown as **horizontal scrollable chip bar** — no wrapping, keeps vertical space free.
